I want to build a device that sits in my computer and allows me to remotely turn it on or off
20:50
Put together a prototype
Michael 09/11/2022 20:51
that should be very simple
RaduTek 09/11/2022 20:51
An ESP8266 WiFi microcontroller hooked up to the motherboard's power button pin and some code to set up an HTTP Server
20:51
It's now basically a remote power switch over the internet
20:52
But I want to make it more advanced, so that it knows the state of the computer
20:52
Either by sensing the power from a Molex connector
20:52
Or by maybe having a service on the PC send a status message over Serial
20:53
As the ESP board will just be connected to the motherboard USB header so it gets power and data
20:53
And I can flash it while it's sitting in the PC, just make sure not to have it turn off the PC when it's not supposed to
20:54
I measured the 2 power button pins of my mobo
20:54
One is common ground and the other is the input pin, held active high to 3.3 volts
20:54
So I just have the MCU pull down the pin then float it back
